{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-19",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_19_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "The Russian's Hand",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 7,
  "page_total": 10,
  "page_start_sec": 1496.7,
  "page_end_sec": 1737.62,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.559,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 1496.7,
      "end": 1499.52,
      "text": "He took a silk handkerchief from his pocket and"
    },
    {
      "start": 1499.52,
      "end": 1500.44,
      "text": "put it to his mouth."
    },
    {
      "start": 1501.28,
      "end": 1502.8,
      "text": "It came away daubed with blood.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1503.88,
      "end": 1505.48,
      "text": "He put it to his mouth once more and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1505.56,
      "end": 1507.0,
      "text": "looked reproachfully at the boy."
    },
    {
      "start": 1507.3,
      "end": 1508.98,
      "text": "The boy snarled,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1509.48,
      "end": 1510.52,
      "text": "keep away from me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1511.04,
      "end": 1512.22,
      "text": "and put his face between his"
    },
    {
      "start": 1512.22,
      "end": 1512.78,
      "text": "hands again."
    },
    {
      "start": 1513.792,
      "end": 1516.72,
      "text": "Kyra's handkerchief released the fragrance of shipra in the room.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1517.728,
      "end": 1518.42,
      "text": "Kyra's cry had",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1518.56,
      "end": 1520.34,
      "text": "brought Bridget O'Shaughnessy to the door."
    },
    {
      "start": 1520.66,
      "end": 1521.38,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1521.44,
      "end": 1521.88,
      "text": "grinning,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1521.9,
      "end": 1523.88,
      "text": "jerked a thumb at the sofa and told her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1524.26,
      "end": 1525.7,
      "text": "the chorus of true love,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1525.93,
      "end": 1527.46,
      "text": "how's the food coming along?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1528.54,
      "end": 1528.92,
      "text": "It's coming,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1529.08,
      "end": 1529.64,
      "text": "she said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1529.78,
      "end": 1530.6,
      "text": "and went back to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1530.6,
      "end": 1531.0,
      "text": "the kitchen."
    },
    {
      "start": 1532.064,
      "end": 1533.88,
      "text": "Spade lighted his cigarette and addressed Gutman.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1534.1,
      "end": 1535.58,
      "text": "Let's talk about money."
    },
    {
      "start": 1536.54,
      "end": 1537.04,
      "text": "Willingly,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1537.04,
      "end": 1537.34,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1537.5,
      "end": 1538.42,
      "text": "with all my heart,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1538.82,
      "end": 1539.58,
      "text": "the fat man replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1540.32,
      "end": 1541.7,
      "text": "but I might as well tell you frankly",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1541.8,
      "end": 1544.38,
      "text": "right now that 10,000 is every cent I can raise."
    },
    {
      "start": 1545.472,
      "end": 1546.44,
      "text": "Spade exhaled smoke.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1547.26,
      "end": 1548.14,
      "text": "I thought to have 20.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1548.68,
      "end": 1549.86,
      "text": "I wish you could."
    },
    {
      "start": 1550.74,
      "end": 1552.52,
      "text": "I'd give it to you gladly if I had it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1552.56,
      "end": 1555.24,
      "text": "but $10,000 is every cent I can manage,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1555.38,
      "end": 1556.58,
      "text": "on my word of honor."
    },
    {
      "start": 1557.6,
      "end": 1557.94,
      "text": "Of course,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1557.94,
      "end": 1558.2,
      "text": "sir,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1558.32,
      "end": 1558.96,
      "text": "you understand."
    },
    {
      "start": 1559.66,
      "end": 1561.0,
      "text": "That is simply the first payment.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1561.6,
      "end": 1561.88,
      "text": "Later.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1563.168,
      "end": 1563.66,
      "text": "Spade laughed.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1564.38,
      "end": 1566.14,
      "text": "I know you'll give me millions later,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1566.3,
      "end": 1566.72,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1566.84,
      "end": 1567.82,
      "text": "but let's stick to"
    },
    {
      "start": 1567.82,
      "end": 1568.88,
      "text": "this first payment now."
    },
    {
      "start": 1569.632,
      "end": 1570.42,
      "text": "$15,000.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1571.328,
      "end": 1572.62,
      "text": "Gutman smiled and frowned,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1572.7,
      "end": 1573.82,
      "text": "and shook his head."
    },
    {
      "start": 1574.12,
      "end": 1574.74,
      "text": "Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1574.88,
      "end": 1575.24,
      "text": "Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1575.4,
      "end": 1578.54,
      "text": "I've told you frankly and candidly and on my word"
    },
    {
      "start": 1578.54,
      "end": 1581.54,
      "text": "of honor as a gentleman that $10,000 is all the"
    },
    {
      "start": 1581.54,
      "end": 1582.36,
      "text": "money I've got,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1582.48,
      "end": 1583.36,
      "text": "every penny,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1583.52,
      "end": 1584.96,
      "text": "and all I can raise."
    },
    {
      "start": 1585.94,
      "end": 1587.01,
      "text": "But you didn't say positively.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1588.48,
      "end": 1589.22,
      "text": "Gutman laughed and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1589.34,
      "end": 1589.52,
      "text": "said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1589.58,
      "end": 1590.34,
      "text": "positively."
    },
    {
      "start": 1591.808,
      "end": 1592.7,
      "text": "Spade said gloomily,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1592.94,
      "end": 1594.54,
      "text": "that's not any too good,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1594.64,
      "end": 1596.46,
      "text": "but if it's the best you can do,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1596.64,
      "end": 1597.34,
      "text": "give it to me."
    },
    {
      "start": 1598.464,
      "end": 1599.7,
      "text": "Gutman handed him the envelope.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1600.8,
      "end": 1602.64,
      "text": "Spade counted the bills and was putting them",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1602.82,
      "end": 1605.92,
      "text": "in his pocket when Bridget O'Shaughnessy came in carrying a tray."
    },
    {
      "start": 1606.37,
      "end": 1607.74,
      "text": "The boy would not eat."
    },
    {
      "start": 1608.352,
      "end": 1608.8,
      "text": "Cairo took",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1608.8,
      "end": 1609.7,
      "text": "a cup of coffee."
    },
    {
      "start": 1610.4,
      "end": 1610.84,
      "text": "The girl,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1610.94,
      "end": 1611.86,
      "text": "Gutman and Spade,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1612.02,
      "end": 1613.14,
      "text": "ate the scrambled eggs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1613.38,
      "end": 1613.8,
      "text": "bacon,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1614.04,
      "end": 1614.58,
      "text": "toast,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1614.72,
      "end": 1615.28,
      "text": "and marmalade"
    },
    {
      "start": 1615.28,
      "end": 1618.42,
      "text": "she had prepared and drank two cups of coffee apiece."
    },
    {
      "start": 1619.18,
      "end": 1620.8,
      "text": "Then they settled down to wait the rest",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1620.8,
      "end": 1621.5,
      "text": "of the night through."
    },
    {
      "start": 1622.496,
      "end": 1626.08,
      "text": "Gutman smoked a cigar and read celebrated criminal cases of America,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1626.72,
      "end": 1629.04,
      "text": "now and then chuckling over or commenting on",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1629.04,
      "end": 1631.2,
      "text": "the parts of its contents that amused him."
    },
    {
      "start": 1632.192,
      "end": 1635.06,
      "text": "Cairo nursed his mouth and sulked on his end of the sofa.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1635.92,
      "end": 1637.52,
      "text": "The boy sat with his head in his hands",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1637.52,
      "end": 1639.12,
      "text": "until a little after four o'clock."
    },
    {
      "start": 1639.82,
      "end": 1641.94,
      "text": "Then he laid down with his feet towards Cairo,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1642.46,
      "end": 1643.72,
      "text": "turned his face to the window,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1643.74,
      "end": 1644.5,
      "text": "and went to sleep."
    },
    {
      "start": 1645.472,
      "end": 1647.82,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy in the armchair dozed,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1648.192,
      "end": 1649.48,
      "text": "listened to the fat man's comments,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1649.92,
      "end": 1651.32,
      "text": "and carried on wide-spaced,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1651.34,
      "end": 1653.26,
      "text": "desultory conversations with Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 1654.24,
      "end": 1656.06,
      "text": "Spade rolled and smoked cigarettes and moved,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1656.58,
      "end": 1657.92,
      "text": "without fidgeting or nervousness,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1657.96,
      "end": 1658.66,
      "text": "around the room."
    },
    {
      "start": 1659.14,
      "end": 1661.84,
      "text": "he sat sometimes on an arm of the girl's chair"
    },
    {
      "start": 1661.84,
      "end": 1664.48,
      "text": "on the table corner on the floor at her feet"
    },
    {
      "start": 1664.68,
      "end": 1667.54,
      "text": "on a straight back chair he was wide awake"
    },
    {
      "start": 1667.54,
      "end": 1671.1,
      "text": "cheerful and full of vigor at half past five"
    },
    {
      "start": 1671.1,
      "end": 1673.16,
      "text": "he went into the kitchen and made more coffee"
    },
    {
      "start": 1674.04,
      "end": 1676.54,
      "text": "half an hour later the boy stirred awakened and",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1676.68,
      "end": 1680.46,
      "text": "sat up yawning gutman looked at his watch and questioned spade"
    },
    {
      "start": 1681.2,
      "end": 1681.96,
      "text": "can you get it now",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1683.1,
      "end": 1683.32,
      "text": "give me",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1683.42,
      "end": 1684.04,
      "text": "another hour."
    },
    {
      "start": 1684.64,
      "end": 1686.78,
      "text": "Gutman nodded and went back to his book.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1687.04,
      "end": 1688.4,
      "text": "At seven o'clock,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1688.46,
      "end": 1689.68,
      "text": "Spade went to the telephone"
    },
    {
      "start": 1689.68,
      "end": 1691.2,
      "text": "and called Effie Perrine's number."
    },
    {
      "start": 1691.6,
      "end": 1692.22,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1692.46,
      "end": 1693.14,
      "text": "Mrs."
    },
    {
      "start": 1693.22,
      "end": 1693.6,
      "text": "Perrine?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1693.88,
      "end": 1694.88,
      "text": "This is Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 1695.04,
      "end": 1695.44,
      "text": "Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 1696.2,
      "end": 1696.9,
      "text": "Will you let me talk",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1696.9,
      "end": 1697.38,
      "text": "to Effie,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1697.44,
      "end": 1697.8,
      "text": "please?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1698.06,
      "end": 1698.16,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1699.08,
      "end": 1699.52,
      "text": "it is.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1699.7,
      "end": 1700.34,
      "text": "Thanks."
    },
    {
      "start": 1701.42,
      "end": 1703.44,
      "text": "He whistled two lines of Encuba softly.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1703.84,
      "end": 1703.94,
      "text": "Hello,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1704.62,
      "end": 1704.84,
      "text": "Angel.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1705.04,
      "end": 1705.68,
      "text": "Sorry"
    },
    {
      "start": 1705.68,
      "end": 1706.4,
      "text": "to get you up."
    },
    {
      "start": 1706.58,
      "end": 1707.34,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1707.44,
      "end": 1707.86,
      "text": "very."
    },
    {
      "start": 1708.47,
      "end": 1709.66,
      "text": "Here's the plot.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1710.38,
      "end": 1712.26,
      "text": "In our Holland box at the post office,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1712.38,
      "end": 1712.86,
      "text": "you'll find an"
    },
    {
      "start": 1713.0,
      "end": 1714.58,
      "text": "envelope addressed in my scribble."
    },
    {
      "start": 1715.46,
      "end": 1718.46,
      "text": "There's a Pickwick stage parcel room check in it for the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1718.46,
      "end": 1719.46,
      "text": "bundle we got yesterday."
    },
    {
      "start": 1719.91,
      "end": 1722.02,
      "text": "Will you get the bundle and bring it to me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1722.2,
      "end": 1722.65,
      "text": "PDQ?"
    },
    {
      "start": 1723.2,
      "end": 1723.9,
      "text": "Yes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 1724.02,
      "end": 1724.5,
      "text": "I'm home."
    },
    {
      "start": 1724.74,
      "end": 1725.54,
      "text": "That's the"
    },
    {
      "start": 1725.66,
      "end": 1725.9,
      "text": "girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 1726.06,
      "end": 1726.68,
      "text": "Hustle."
    },
    {
      "start": 1726.78,
      "end": 1726.912,
      "text": "Bye."
    },
    {
      "start": 1727.82,
      "end": 1731.2,
      "text": "The street door bell rang at ten minutes of eight."
    },
    {
      "start": 1731.904,
      "end": 1732.92,
      "text": "Spade went to the telephone",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 1733.04,
      "end": 1735.04,
      "text": "box and pressed the button that released the lock."
    },
    {
      "start": 1735.904,
      "end": 1737.62,
      "text": "Gutman put down his book and rose smiling.",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}